Isolated anterior uveitis in a child with acquired immunodeficiency syndrome.
 A ten-year-old boy with a four-year history of symptomatic human immunodeficiency virus infection had granulomatous iridocyclitis that subsequently resolved with topical corticosteroid and cycloplegic therapy.
 This is the first report, to our knowledge, of isolated anterior uveitis in a child with acquired immunodeficiency syndrome.
